description:
YAHGZ: The Craynobi Tales

Welcome back to the adventure! Feel the magic of tales from long ago. Listen to the stories of the legendary...CRAYBI CRAYNOBI...as he tells his tales of great adventures! What are the secrets of the land of YAHGZ? How did Captain Camel and Crayski meet? What is the Giant Green Gorilla? Why is CrayZilla back again? Why does Crayski have pink hair and a pointy nose? Join Us for the next chapter in the world of the Crays while the Crays pack for their new journey! Secret Origins revealed! Great jumping on point for all AW YEAH COMICS fans! Guest starring The Yahgeez, the Weezerd, and the Wee Kiwi. Originally self-published by Art Baltazar in 1999 by BlindWolf/Electric Milk Comics! AW YEAH Originals!
name: YAHGZ: The Craynobi Tales

description:
The House of Bones, part 3

Lilia is about to go through the mysterious House of Bones to find her "color" and harness the ink that's raging inside her. But her mind gets out of control, wandering around the mysterious House of Bones, while her body reacts in the most unpredictable way, getting out of the shackle, injuring Nightingale, emitting some sort of deadly beams out of her. And so now only Sasha can stop this madness...
name: The House of Bones Part 3

description: Elanor and Clara find themselves in danger. Still working to find Elanor, Isaac and Osrick seek out special help. Booth runs into an old friend.

Get the 7th and FINAL issue of the NSFW zom-com series where flawed male fantasy becomes a nightmare!

Last chapter, Ace found that his friend Gwen had finally succumbed to the lesbian zombie disease. When shooting her wasn't enough, he was forced to to accept his greatest shame as his greatest strength. In order to save Gwen and the rest of the town, Ace now will use it in the final showdown against the alien Space Queen who started it all. Will he be a hero, or will he lose his dick like all the others before him?

Artie is a droid programmed to endlessly perform a single task left in a world abandoned by humans. He is starting to wonder what meaning his task has. But when he and his only friend, Owen, a robotic bird, cast aside the only lives they've ever known in search of a brighter future, they encounter others that want nothing but to hold tight to the past. Join Artie the Robot and Owen the Vulture for a light-hearted sci-fi adventure as they journey far and wide for the answer to one of life's greatest questions: "why are we here?"

Note: The digital edition (3/29/2017) for this volume was released before the print edition.

description:
The Right Reasons

Thomas Simmons was working on an experimental suit his father built when an explosion burned him alive. However, Thomas survived thanks to the suit he was working on and got help from two strangers, Nightstar and Shin and became a superhero known as Nightfighter. Together they now fight for all those who can't fight on their own. After a run-in with Norman Anborn who poisoned the city's water supply, Nightfighter was attacked by A.D.S. troops investigating the case. He lost that fight and got shot in the head...
name: The Right Reasons

description:
Hunting Mantis, Part 1

Jara Bint Rih got injured during World War 3 and spent the last three years of her life in search of a suit she hoped would restore her ability to walk. She and her best friend Lucia Mason found the suit when they were attacked by a gang. But Jara managed to fend the gang off by using the suit. Now, as Shade, she fights to bring down Meta Systems, a multi-billion dollar corporation doing human experiments and building war machines and its boss, the one responsible for her injury in the first place: Ashley Simmons.
name: Hunting Mantis, Part 1

description: A one of a kind, kung fu action epic directed by the inimitable Kaare Andrews! Danny Rand, a.k.a. Iron Fist, is haunted by the consequences of choosing death over life. But when he receives a message from his mystical homeland of K'un Lun, he must return and relive his blood-soaked origin of betrayal and vengeance! The mystical city will be reduced to ruins, while Rand Tower will face a hostile takeover - very hostile! With the wolves at the door and the villain behind it all terribly close to Danny's heart, will he be broken beyond repair? Or can he summon up the will to once again render his shattered hands like unto fists of iron? Hope is reborn with talons and fire, but revenge is a weapon that cuts both ways. Will Danny survive the bloodletting? Collecting IRON FIST: THE LIVING WEAPON #1-12.
name: TPB

It's getting so you can't tell the players without a scorecard.
